sentences: Togolok Moldo (Kyrgyz: Тоголок Молдо; real name: Байымбет Абдырахманов, Bayymbet Abdyrakhmanov; 10 June 1860 – 4 January 1942) was a Kyrgyz poet, Manaschi and folk song writer.
Born in the village Kurtka in what is now the Ak-Talaa District, Naryn Region, Kyrgyzstan.
Togolok Moldo by his audiences – "togolok" means round-faced, "moldo" means an educated person.
A 'Semetey', totalling around 2050 lines, was collected from him by Kayum Miftakov in 1922.
